
Modify your pochoir path in the script (I put a comment in the script)
Run the script and it will ask you for the problem dimention and the problem name (heat_2D_NP for example)

Then:

Optimization flags used in Makefile:
OPT_FLAGS = -O3 -DNDEBUG -Wall -fpermissive  -Wall  -Wno-unknown-pragmas  -std=c++0x -lrt -fcilkplus -lcilkrts


Flags in PMain.hs
iccFlags = ["-O3", "-DNDEBUG", "-std=c++0x", "-Wall", "-Werror", "-lcilkrts", "-fcilkplus"]
iccPPFlags = ["-E", "-C", "-P", "-DNCHECK_SHAPE", "-DNDEBUG", "-std=c++0x", "-Wall", "-Werror",  "-lcilkrts", "-fcilkplus", "-o"]


Macros in pochoir_common.hpp:
#define USE_PROJECTION
//#define GENEITY_TEST
//#define KERNEL_SELECTION
#define AUTO_TUNE
//#define TIME_INVARIANCE_INTERIOR
#define TIME_INVARIANCE_BOUNDARY

You will need to remove lamda fucntion outside of the main file and make them a normal fucntion.

